1
00:01:35,067 --> 00:01:37,902
[Episode 8]

2
00:01:47,834 --> 00:01:49,434
Mr. Sheng.

3
00:01:50,503 --> 00:01:52,337
How do you feel?

4
00:02:05,137 --> 00:02:06,805
I'm fine.

5
00:02:10,990 --> 00:02:12,592
Was anyone else hurt?

6
00:02:12,592 --> 00:02:15,094
Just one colleague twisted their ankle
on the way out.

7
00:02:15,094 --> 00:02:16,462
They've already been approved
for medical leave.

8
00:02:16,462 --> 00:02:18,998
No other serious issues.

9
00:02:18,998 --> 00:02:20,500
Okay.

10
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:22,134
Good to hear.

11
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:30,576
Dr. Wang, what's wrong with Mr. Sheng?

12
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:32,946
The blood test results are back.

13
00:02:32,946 --> 00:02:36,215
Our preliminary diagnosis
is pheromone dysregulation syndrome.

14
00:02:36,215 --> 00:02:37,583
What?

15
00:02:37,583 --> 00:02:38,785
His free-type pheromone level, type T,

16
00:02:38,785 --> 00:02:41,087
is more than five times the normal range.

17
00:02:41,087 --> 00:02:43,956
That's extremely abnormal for an Alpha.

18
00:02:43,956 --> 00:02:48,126
Even Omegas only reach that level during heat.

19
00:02:48,761 --> 00:02:50,997
Is it serious?

20
00:02:50,997 --> 00:02:52,865
How do we treat it?

21
00:02:52,865 --> 00:02:57,770
To be honest, given Mr. Sheng's age
and S-class Alpha status,

22
00:02:57,770 --> 00:02:59,772
he shouldn't be developing this.

23
00:02:59,772 --> 00:03:02,175
But considering his high stress,

24
00:03:02,175 --> 00:03:05,578
long working hours, and irregular routines,

25
00:03:05,578 --> 00:03:08,981
we have to take the possibility seriously.

26
00:03:10,016 --> 00:03:13,419
For now, I'll prescribe oral medication

27
00:03:13,419 --> 00:03:18,825
to prevent extreme overflow
that could harm others.

28
00:03:18,825 --> 00:03:20,993
Let's wait until he's hospitalized

29
00:03:20,993 --> 00:03:22,895
and conduct a comprehensive inspection.

30
00:03:22,895 --> 00:03:24,496
Hospitalized?

31
00:03:26,165 --> 00:03:27,667
Can't I just take the meds?

32
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:30,870
Mr. Sheng, I know you're busy,

33
00:03:30,870 --> 00:03:33,439
but your body belongs to you.

34
00:03:33,439 --> 00:03:37,944
Pheromone dysregulation
is a serious endocrine disorder.

35
00:03:37,944 --> 00:03:40,879
We still don't fully understand the cause.

36
00:03:42,849 --> 00:03:45,718
And it's already mid-stage
on your first checkup.

37
00:03:45,718 --> 00:03:47,686
Please take this seriously.

38
00:03:50,223 --> 00:03:52,457
But I don't have the time to be hospitalized.

39
00:03:53,159 --> 00:03:56,562
It's your body and your time.

40
00:03:56,562 --> 00:03:59,565
But as your doctor, this is my honest advice.

41
00:03:59,565 --> 00:04:02,869
At this point,
I don't think you're fit for discharge.

42
00:04:02,869 --> 00:04:04,636
Thank you, Doctor.

43
00:04:05,872 --> 00:04:07,472
- Mr. Sheng.
- Let's go.

44
00:04:09,509 --> 00:04:12,844
You should stay in the hospital and rest.

45
00:04:18,518 --> 00:04:19,852
Fine.

46
00:04:19,852 --> 00:04:22,355
Then I want daily summaries of meetings

47
00:04:22,355 --> 00:04:24,056
and project updates delivered to me.

48
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:27,159
Don't worry, I'll have everything organized,

49
00:04:27,159 --> 00:04:29,362
and report to you every day.

50
00:04:29,362 --> 00:04:30,596
Okay.

51
00:04:30,596 --> 00:04:34,800
And don't tell anyone that I'm hospitalized.

52
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,469
Yes, sir.

53
00:04:36,469 --> 00:04:38,070
Good.

54
00:06:11,264 --> 00:06:12,531
Come in.

55
00:06:17,403 --> 00:06:18,904
Mr. Sheng.

56
00:06:18,904 --> 00:06:21,039
These are flowers from Mr. Hua.

57
00:06:24,677 --> 00:06:27,747
