120
00:10:25,251 --> 00:10:27,152
Thanks, Dr. Wang.

121
00:10:27,152 --> 00:10:28,920
You're welcome.

122
00:10:35,027 --> 00:10:38,830
Seems like you're my lucky star.

123
00:10:39,531 --> 00:10:41,199
What?

124
00:10:43,936 --> 00:10:46,839
I feel much better after seeing you.

125
00:10:46,839 --> 00:10:49,275
I'm not as tired, and my headaches are gone.

126
00:10:49,275 --> 00:10:51,677
The doctor says I can be discharged next week.

127
00:10:51,677 --> 00:10:53,945
Aren't you my lucky star?

128
00:11:13,999 --> 00:11:15,401
Getting discharged on a rest day is perfect.

129
00:11:15,401 --> 00:11:16,835
Take a day to rest at home.

130
00:11:16,835 --> 00:11:21,507
There will be live-streamed biopharma
innovation forum on Monday, 10 A.M.

131
00:11:21,507 --> 00:11:25,010
At 2 P.M., you have afternoon tea
with X Holdings' executive.

132
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:28,547
Don't worry, I'll remind you again.

133
00:11:28,547 --> 00:11:29,682
Good.

134
00:11:29,682 --> 00:11:32,151
Thanks, Secretary Chen. Have a good weekend.

135
00:11:32,151 --> 00:11:33,752
You, too.

136
00:11:39,491 --> 00:11:41,327
Mr. Sheng, how do you feel?

137
00:11:41,327 --> 00:11:42,994
Any discomfort?

138
00:11:43,829 --> 00:11:45,364
